# Git Usage

## Commit Message Format

Use conventional commit prefixes:

| Prefix | Usage |
|---|---|
| `fix:` | Bug fixes |
| `feat:` | New features |
| `perf:` | Performance improvements |
| `docs:` | Documentation changes |
| `style:` | Formatting changes (no logic change) |
| `refactor:` | Code refactoring (no behavior change) |
| `test:` | Adding or updating tests |
| `chore:` | Maintenance tasks (deps, config, CI) |

## Rules

- Write commit messages in imperative mood: `fix: resolve wallet disconnect crash` not `fixed the crash`
- Keep the first line under 72 characters
- Add a blank line + body for complex changes
- Reference issue numbers when applicable: `fix: handle null balance (#42)`
- One logical change per commit — don't mix refactoring with features

```
feat: add sign message form with signature display

- Created SignMessageForm component with text input
- Integrated useWalletActions hook for signing
- Shows hex-encoded signature on success
```

## Branch Naming

- `feat/description` for features
- `fix/description` for bug fixes
- `chore/description` for maintenance
